    "description": "The strategy is a long only, cross sectional momentum rotation within large, liquid US technology equities, designed to capture persistent medium term trend while controlling risk through volatility scaling and hard loss limits. Each month, it ranks a technology universe on 90d price momentum and invests only in stocks with positive momentum, selecting the top 10. Positions are sized using inverse 20-day realized volatility, so higher volatility names receive smaller weights.\n\nRebalancing occurs",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a long only, cross sectional momentum rotation within large, liquid US technology equities, designed to capture persistent medium term trend while controlling risk through volatility scaling and hard loss limits. Each month, it ranks a technology universe on 90d price momentum and invests only in stocks with positive momentum, selecting the top 10. Positions are sized using inverse 20-day realized volatility, so higher volatility names receive smaller weights.\n\nRebalancing occurs monthly at the start of each month, with a 100 day warm up to initialize indicators. Risk is managed with a per-position stop loss that liquidates any holding whose unrealized loss exceeds 2 percent of total portfolio value. Any residual capital (for example due to insufficient qualifying momentum names or stop outs) is allocated to gold via GLD as a defensive cash substitute, with a daily cash sweep that tops up GLD when equity exposure drops materially.",
